<subSubSection pageNumber="577" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="577">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="577">Note:</emphasis>
Terrell (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="577">Rhodora</emphasis>
61: 168. 1959) evidently regarded material on 128.2 (LINN) as the type, but this collection was a later addition to the herbarium, and ineligible. Reveal &amp; al. designated what is evidently 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="577">Clayton 63</emphasis>
(BM) as 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
, despite describing it as 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="577">Clayton 506.</emphasis>
Subsequently, Terrell (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="577">Syst. Bot. Monogr.</emphasis>
48: 50. 1996) has rejected their choice in favour of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="577">Clayton 63</emphasis>
, but it seems clear that both are talking about the same sheet and there has merely been confusion over labelling.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
